WEBVTT

00:10.605 --> 00:11.834
<i>Previously on</i> Dexter:

00:12.045 --> 00:13.798
Who's the guy that dropped you off?

00:14.005 --> 00:15.519
We didn't sleep together.

00:15.725 --> 00:17.762
You are certainly allowed
to be a player.

00:19.285 --> 00:21.197
You remember Cassie, right?
Yeah.

00:21.405 --> 00:22.441
New neighbour. Hi.
Hi.

00:22.645 --> 00:24.125
I kind of need to leave.

00:24.325 --> 00:26.760
I'll take care of Jamie.
Maybe we could reschedule?

00:27.005 --> 00:28.564
Yeah. I'd like that.

00:29.045 --> 00:30.877
Any reason why you
haven't taken the exam?

00:31.085 --> 00:33.964
I got your brother on my ass
about taking the sergeant's test—

00:34.165 --> 00:36.236
What is so wrong about
bettering yourself?

00:36.445 --> 00:37.640
You nailed it, bro.

00:37.845 --> 00:41.236
Is he your choice for sergeant?
I'm ready for more responsibility.

00:41.445 --> 00:43.835
I want you to strongly consider
making her sergeant.

00:44.045 --> 00:45.365
I think you may be my father.

00:45.605 --> 00:49.155
Family showing up out of nowhere?
A lot of times, they want something.

00:49.405 --> 00:51.556
I you to do a background check
on someone.

00:51.765 --> 00:54.325
You think she's here to rip you off?
I don't know.

00:54.725 --> 00:55.841
Norma Rivera.

00:56.045 --> 00:58.799
She'd been having an affair
with the boss, Ed Hamilton.

00:59.005 --> 01:00.962
Dad, what's going on?
The Hamilton's son.

01:01.205 --> 01:03.356
Did you go to where
Norma Rivera was killed?

01:03.565 --> 01:06.763
I did.
What did you see in your analysis?

01:07.005 --> 01:08.803
Leave the kid alone.
He killed her.

01:09.045 --> 01:11.196
You don't know that.
Your only witness recanted.

01:11.405 --> 01:13.761
No reason to make enemies
unless we really have to.

01:13.965 --> 01:15.797
Where's Yates?

01:16.005 --> 01:18.804
So this is finally over.
My tormenter's dead.

01:19.005 --> 01:21.281
Thanks to you, Dexter.
And Deb.

01:21.485 --> 01:23.716
I'm glad you found your way
back to each other.

01:23.925 --> 01:25.803
Well, the family that kills together...

01:26.005 --> 01:28.964
A few days ago, everything seemed
hopeless between Deb and me.

01:29.165 --> 01:31.441
But through Dr. Vogel,
I've got my sister back.

01:31.645 --> 01:33.125
It's beautiful out here, Dexter.

01:33.365 --> 01:34.924
I wanted to be with family.

01:36.005 --> 01:42.079
FaceTime with British Models 24/7
www. saucytime. com

03:37.525 --> 03:38.800
<i>Accidents happen,</i>

03:39.005 --> 03:41.156
<i>shattering our sense of control,</i>

03:41.405 --> 03:43.283
<i>if not our lives.</i>

03:46.605 --> 03:49.040
<i>It's no accident
that Zach Hamilton is here.</i>

03:49.245 --> 03:52.124
<i>He's drawn to blood, like me.</i>

03:53.645 --> 03:56.524
<i>Did he kill Norma Rivera?</i>

04:07.765 --> 04:11.361
<i>After a week of vetting him, I haven't
been able to find definitive proof.</i>

04:17.525 --> 04:21.678
<i>But I'm sure if I keep following him
the truth will become clear.</i>

04:38.925 --> 04:40.564
<i>Or it could get murkier.</i>

05:14.965 --> 05:16.081
Dexter.

05:16.285 --> 05:18.436
Have you taken on
Zach Hamilton as a patient?

05:18.645 --> 05:19.840
It's nice to see you too.

05:20.045 --> 05:23.163
I have to protect you from another
murderer? How did he get to you?

05:23.645 --> 05:24.965
His father contacted me

05:25.165 --> 05:28.920
because of my reputation
for working with psychopaths.

05:29.165 --> 05:33.239
He's concerned about his son's
behaviour, his propensity for violence.

05:33.445 --> 05:34.879
It's more than a propensity.

05:35.085 --> 05:38.317
I think Zach Hamilton
killed Norma Rivera.

05:39.445 --> 05:42.483
And I take it that
you followed him here today

05:42.685 --> 05:44.677
because you're planning
to kill him?

05:44.885 --> 05:48.083
The thought had crossed my mind,
yes, if I can find solid proof.

05:48.565 --> 05:51.876
Well, then it would seem
that we have a conflict of interest.

05:54.245 --> 05:56.202
I don't believe this.

05:57.205 --> 06:00.721
You're going to work with another killer
after what happened with Yates?

06:01.085 --> 06:03.839
Dexter, I appreciate your concern,

06:04.045 --> 06:07.834
but I'm not going to talk about
Zach Hamilton with you any further.

06:08.725 --> 06:10.125
It wouldn't be ethical.

06:10.325 --> 06:12.442
Suddenly,
you're worried about ethics?

06:12.685 --> 06:15.075
I know. I threw them out
the window when I met you

06:15.285 --> 06:17.356
because my life was on the line.

06:17.645 --> 06:19.523
Now the threat is over.

06:19.725 --> 06:21.921
You're bringing another threat
into your life.

06:22.125 --> 06:25.402
It's my work. What can I say?

06:25.885 --> 06:27.956
I treat dangerous people.

06:28.205 --> 06:29.798
It's a hazard of the job.

06:30.005 --> 06:31.519
Besides, you have no proof

06:31.725 --> 06:33.956
that Zach Hamilton
is guilty of anything.

06:34.685 --> 06:35.801
I will.

06:36.285 --> 06:37.639
If you do,

06:37.845 --> 06:39.802
then come to see me first,

06:40.045 --> 06:41.559
before you do anything,

06:41.765 --> 06:44.200
and we'll have
another conversation.

06:45.325 --> 06:47.237
Would you do me that favour?

06:48.405 --> 06:49.964
We'll see.

07:02.445 --> 07:04.914
Maybe this is why
she tracked me down, for money.

07:05.125 --> 07:06.878
You don't know that.

07:07.085 --> 07:09.645
I mean, maybe she genuinely
wanted to get to know you.

07:09.845 --> 07:12.565
What, at the same time
her Hyundai's being repossessed?

07:12.765 --> 07:15.075
Has she asked you for money?
No.

07:15.285 --> 07:18.562
But she always seems to be missing
her purse when the check comes.

07:23.045 --> 07:26.595
I thought we had a real connection.
You like having Niki in your life?

07:27.805 --> 07:29.637
I do.
Then why don't you wait it out

07:29.885 --> 07:32.002
and see how it plays out?

07:32.285 --> 07:35.119
In the meantime,
you can enjoy her company.

07:38.285 --> 07:39.639
Okay.

07:46.045 --> 07:47.604
Hm, heh.
Thanks, Deb.

07:47.765 --> 07:49.404
Welcome.

07:51.645 --> 07:54.365
Deb, got a new case.

07:55.565 --> 07:59.525
Let me guess, someone suspects their
significant other is fucking around.

08:00.125 --> 08:03.516
Yeah, but this one
is a bit different.

08:03.725 --> 08:06.524
How?
Because the person is me

08:06.725 --> 08:08.205
and the significant other

08:08.405 --> 08:11.045
is my sister's ass-chasing,
shithead boyfriend.

08:11.245 --> 08:13.077
Kevin Wyman, notorious player,

08:13.285 --> 08:16.198
frequents a singles bar in a hotel
where he keeps a suite.

08:17.005 --> 08:18.883
Have you tried talking to her?

08:19.085 --> 08:20.155
Susan doesn't listen to me.

08:20.365 --> 08:22.596
It'd just push her
more quickly into his arms.

08:22.805 --> 08:24.034
So that's off the table.

08:24.245 --> 08:27.761
Well, going behind her back
seems kind of fucked up.

08:27.965 --> 08:30.685
It's gotta be this way.
I gotta catch this guy in the act.

08:30.885 --> 08:32.604
Okay, but you're doing it
by yourself.

08:32.805 --> 08:34.205
I need your help on this, Deb.

08:34.365 --> 08:35.515
It'd be a lot less conspicuous

08:35.685 --> 08:37.404
if we work this as a couple.

08:37.605 --> 08:39.756
Well, I'm not sure if I'm comfortable.

08:39.965 --> 08:42.161
Well, are you comfortable
getting a pay cheque?

08:45.525 --> 08:46.800
Okay, boss.

08:48.765 --> 08:50.438
Thank you.

08:53.605 --> 08:55.676
Where does this piece go?

08:57.045 --> 08:58.764
Right here.

08:59.485 --> 09:00.805
Very good.

09:01.005 --> 09:02.598
Dex?

09:02.845 --> 09:05.360
Don't forget, my birthday picnic's
in a few days, okay?

09:05.605 --> 09:08.074
On the beach, outside of Papa's.
Bring Harrison.

09:08.285 --> 09:10.163
Yeah, we'll be there.
Great.

09:10.405 --> 09:13.318
You know who else
will be there? Cassie.

09:13.525 --> 09:14.754
I heard you have a date with her.

09:14.965 --> 09:16.081
No, it's not a date.

09:16.325 --> 09:20.160
I felt like I owed her one after we both
bailed on your dinner the other night.

09:20.365 --> 09:22.516
Why won't you just admit
that you like her

09:22.725 --> 09:24.717
and that I am an
awesome matchmaker?

09:24.965 --> 09:28.276
I admit that you're an awesome nanny.
You'll have to settle for that.

09:28.485 --> 09:31.557
We'll revisit this after the date.

09:31.885 --> 09:33.365
Oh, by the way,

09:33.565 --> 09:35.238
the TV remote has

09:35.445 --> 09:36.515
been missing since yesterday.

09:36.765 --> 09:38.438
I think somebody hid it

09:38.685 --> 09:41.519
but I can't get anything
out of him.

09:42.165 --> 09:44.122
Harrison, did you
take the TV remote?

09:44.325 --> 09:45.600
No.

09:45.805 --> 09:48.559
Do you know where it is?
No.

09:49.045 --> 09:50.161
He says he didn't take it.

09:50.405 --> 09:51.475
Right.

09:51.685 --> 09:54.200
Guess I'll just keep looking for it.

09:57.685 --> 10:00.120
Homicide in Liberty City.

10:00.325 --> 10:03.363
It looks like you're gonna have
to finish that puzzle on your own.

10:03.565 --> 10:05.602
I'm doing all the work anyway.

10:06.605 --> 10:08.961
Yeah, you are.

10:09.165 --> 10:11.077
Bye.
Bye.

10:20.045 --> 10:21.764
Welcome to spatter-land.

10:21.965 --> 10:23.319
Hope you brought extra string.

10:23.565 --> 10:25.602
Never leave home without it.

10:27.205 --> 10:28.355
Good news.

10:28.605 --> 10:30.642
We have the victim's boyfriend
in custody.

10:30.845 --> 10:33.314
A witness saw him
taking off from the scene,

10:33.525 --> 10:35.517
and he forgot to change
his bloody socks.

10:35.725 --> 10:37.478
Heh. God bless stupid killers.

10:51.685 --> 10:53.358
<i>Once again, drawn to blood.</i>

10:54.285 --> 10:57.562
<i>Looks like Zach has just given me
the in I need.</i>

11:17.725 --> 11:20.081
Zach Hamilton, right?

11:20.365 --> 11:21.958
You were at my house.

11:22.205 --> 11:23.321
That's right.

11:23.885 --> 11:26.320
You guys find out
who killed Norma?

11:26.845 --> 11:29.679
No luck. It's a dead end.

11:32.325 --> 11:33.805
You like to shoot crime scenes?

11:34.045 --> 11:36.924
Yeah, I got a police scanner
app on my phone.

11:37.125 --> 11:38.605
Better than playing video games.

11:38.845 --> 11:41.599
You ever been on the other side
of the yellow tape?

11:42.125 --> 11:44.765
Nope.
This is as close as I've gotten.

11:45.645 --> 11:47.955
Well, come on.

11:49.805 --> 11:53.116
Are you serious?
Yeah, just don't touch anything.

12:00.965 --> 12:02.558
Whoa.

12:04.525 --> 12:06.437
This is amazing.

12:06.845 --> 12:10.043
<i>I remember that feeling.
Awe, wonder.</i>

12:10.245 --> 12:11.361
<i>It only fed the urge.</i>

12:11.565 --> 12:14.034
Hey, can I take some pictures?

12:15.885 --> 12:19.561
It's usually against protocol,

12:19.805 --> 12:21.034
but what the hell? Go ahead.

12:21.365 --> 12:23.402
Cool. Thanks.

12:25.445 --> 12:28.995
So, what happened to her?

12:29.205 --> 12:30.719
She was stabbed.

12:30.925 --> 12:33.440
Yeah, obviously.
But, like, you know, how?

12:33.925 --> 12:36.724
<i>If I open up to him,
maybe he'll open up to me.</i>

12:36.925 --> 12:38.439
Come on. I can handle it.

12:42.045 --> 12:44.082
Well, the victim
tried to defend herself.

12:44.325 --> 12:46.237
There were defensive
wounds on her body

12:46.445 --> 12:50.564
but you can also tell by these
big, round drops on the ground.

12:54.125 --> 12:56.003
And this multiple cast-off spatter

12:56.205 --> 12:59.357
suggests that she was
stabbed several times.

12:59.565 --> 13:02.285
And the arterial spurting here

13:02.485 --> 13:05.364
indicates that the killer
severed her carotid artery

13:05.565 --> 13:07.238
with the first stab.

13:09.165 --> 13:11.964
You can tell all that
just by looking at the blood?

13:12.845 --> 13:13.995
Pretty much.

13:14.805 --> 13:16.478
Awesome.

13:18.685 --> 13:20.836
So I heard you caught
the guy who did it.

13:21.045 --> 13:22.877
Yeah, her boyfriend.
How?

13:23.085 --> 13:26.078
He was sloppy.
Left a bloody print and DNA.

13:26.325 --> 13:28.476
He was spotted
driving away from the scene.

13:28.685 --> 13:30.358
Oh, yeah? What kind of car?

13:30.565 --> 13:32.921
<i>Must have heard his Porsche
was seen at Norma's apartment.</i>

13:33.165 --> 13:34.360
No one noticed.

13:39.285 --> 13:41.277
So the killer,

13:42.285 --> 13:44.436
he should've worn gloves
and long sleeves,

13:44.645 --> 13:46.125
made sure
he was covered up.

13:46.325 --> 13:49.124
<i>He's making this a teaching moment.</i>

13:49.845 --> 13:52.280
Well, yeah, if he was smart.

13:53.685 --> 13:54.880
<i>The kid's a quick study,</i>

13:55.085 --> 13:57.520
<i>but that doesn't prove
he killed Norma Rivera.</i>

13:59.085 --> 14:03.716
So, hey, I gotta get going,
but thanks.

14:04.405 --> 14:07.637
Hey, why don't you give me a call
when you print those up?

14:07.845 --> 14:09.837
I'd love to take a look.

14:10.565 --> 14:13.524
Yeah.
Yeah, I guess I could do that.

14:18.325 --> 14:20.760
<i>Time to make another connection.</i>

14:26.565 --> 14:29.717
Here you go.
Thank you.

14:29.925 --> 14:32.235
Thank you
for doing this with me.

14:32.445 --> 14:35.563
When you own a food truck, you
have to scope out the competition.

14:35.765 --> 14:37.279
Plus I just really love to eat.

14:37.525 --> 14:38.561
Yeah, no problem.

14:38.765 --> 14:41.041
I wouldn't miss these peanut butter
and Nutella fries for anything.

14:41.245 --> 14:42.759
Mm-hm.

14:48.325 --> 14:50.521
So you're indulging me
in my favourite pastime.

14:50.725 --> 14:52.364
What do you like to do for fun?

14:52.565 --> 14:55.000
You know, normal stuff.

14:55.645 --> 14:57.238
Like what?

14:58.325 --> 15:00.635
Um...
Heh, heh.

15:01.965 --> 15:03.922
I like spending time with my son.

15:04.125 --> 15:06.321
I already know you're
a great dad. What else?

15:08.205 --> 15:09.275
I love my job.

15:09.925 --> 15:12.565
But that's work.
What are you passionate about?

15:15.485 --> 15:16.999
I like to bowl.

15:17.205 --> 15:18.878
You're passionate about bowling?

15:20.885 --> 15:22.683
No. Heh.
Heh, heh.

15:22.885 --> 15:24.683
Of course not.

15:24.885 --> 15:27.480
I just do it for fun, once in a while.

15:29.285 --> 15:32.722
What about your weekends
or your free time?

15:34.165 --> 15:35.645
Oh, I have a boat.

15:35.845 --> 15:37.120
Oh, I love to sail.

15:37.725 --> 15:39.682
No, it's a motorboat.

15:39.885 --> 15:42.002
Oh. You water-ski?

15:42.325 --> 15:43.725
No.

15:43.965 --> 15:46.525
Race?
No.

15:47.365 --> 15:49.038
Do you scuba dive?

15:49.565 --> 15:50.999
No.

15:51.165 --> 15:53.760
Heh, heh.
What do you do on your boat?

15:55.165 --> 15:56.485
I just...

15:56.725 --> 15:59.684
Take it out and...

16:00.565 --> 16:02.557
Turn around and come back.

16:04.045 --> 16:05.081
That's it?

16:05.285 --> 16:07.561
<i>That's all I can tell you.</i>

16:08.125 --> 16:09.798
I think we may need
some alcohol.

16:10.885 --> 16:12.239
Right.

16:13.445 --> 16:16.040
<i>Dating is harder than I remember.</i>

16:23.045 --> 16:24.718
Oh, this guy is fucking pathetic.

16:24.965 --> 16:27.525
I get that you hate the guy,
but looking isn't cheating.

16:27.725 --> 16:29.637
It's a slow night.
Give him a minute.

16:32.525 --> 16:34.244
So you said Susan
doesn't listen.

16:34.445 --> 16:36.914
Does that mean you all
have a strained relationship?

16:37.125 --> 16:38.605
Not from my end, no.

16:39.565 --> 16:41.318
But from hers?

16:42.325 --> 16:43.964
Yeah, you know, probably.

16:44.725 --> 16:47.604
I mean, look, I couldn't wait
to get away from my old man,

16:47.805 --> 16:49.398
and Susan was just a kid.

16:49.605 --> 16:53.565
You know, I should have
at least picked up the phone.

16:54.645 --> 16:57.114
But I never did,
you know, so...

16:59.405 --> 17:01.795
Well, you can't undo the past.

17:03.365 --> 17:06.005
And families fuck you up.
That's just the way it is.

17:07.485 --> 17:10.125
I can stop Susan from fucking up her future.
I can do that.

17:14.085 --> 17:16.520
It looks like he's
packing it in for the night.

17:16.765 --> 17:19.121
If you wanna catch this guy,
why don't I set him up?

17:19.325 --> 17:22.397
We can see if he takes the bait.
No, I don't want you doing that.

17:22.645 --> 17:25.444
I worked Vice. I've done
worse than that before.

17:27.685 --> 17:29.756
I just need pictures
of him hitting on you.

17:29.965 --> 17:31.558
Certainly nothing
more than that.

17:31.765 --> 17:33.119
Are you sure?

17:33.365 --> 17:36.995
I mean, I could marry him,
maybe pop out a couple of babies.

17:38.405 --> 17:39.919
Let's go.

17:56.205 --> 17:58.197
Dexter, thanks for coming.
Sure.

17:58.965 --> 18:00.797
Couldn't wait to show you
these photos.

18:01.005 --> 18:02.917
Yeah, no problem.
It's on my way to work.

18:03.125 --> 18:04.241
Doughnut?

18:05.005 --> 18:06.234
Fucking A.

18:08.205 --> 18:09.241
Mm.

18:11.245 --> 18:12.964
Well?

18:16.045 --> 18:19.356
<i>He treats the blood
like a swimsuit model.</i>

18:20.165 --> 18:21.758
Well,

18:22.485 --> 18:24.124
very colourful.

18:24.325 --> 18:27.875
You know, a lot of photographers
like to mute down their reds.

18:28.125 --> 18:30.799
You know,
find it too distracting,

18:31.045 --> 18:33.355
but I like to ride the saturation.

18:33.525 --> 18:34.800
Hm.

18:36.565 --> 18:38.079
You think I overdid it?

18:38.765 --> 18:40.757
No way. These are you.

18:40.965 --> 18:42.479
That's the important thing.

18:42.725 --> 18:45.365
Well, I can work you up
some prints, if you want.

18:45.605 --> 18:46.959
I wouldn't have them
if it weren't for you.

18:47.165 --> 18:50.317
Actually, I think I have
plenty of my own.

18:52.525 --> 18:53.845
Right.

18:54.045 --> 18:56.480
Of course.
I forget it was a crime scene.

18:56.685 --> 19:00.599
Keep thinking that dead chick
spilled all that blood just for me.

19:07.525 --> 19:08.845
Who's she?

19:10.925 --> 19:12.439
Uh, it's nothing.

19:13.565 --> 19:16.364
Just a lens test.

19:16.565 --> 19:19.080
New 300 millimetre.
Fucking monster.

19:19.285 --> 19:20.275
Wow.

19:22.805 --> 19:24.125
Excuse me.

19:24.285 --> 19:25.685
Yep?

19:33.285 --> 19:37.199
Jesus, you still drunk from last night
or are you starting a new bender?

19:37.445 --> 19:41.075
Yeah, okay. Yeah, I said okay.

19:42.845 --> 19:44.996
Uh, I gotta go.

19:45.245 --> 19:47.441
Anything wrong?
It's fine. I just gotta go.

19:49.565 --> 19:51.124
Sure, some other time then.

19:53.885 --> 19:56.764
<i>I'll have to find another way
to get to him.</i>

20:04.005 --> 20:05.041
Ah, lieutenant.

20:05.245 --> 20:06.998
Tell me something.

20:07.205 --> 20:09.242
Did you decide
you don't need a sergeant?

20:09.445 --> 20:11.880
Sir?
I expected an announcement by now.

20:12.085 --> 20:13.121
What's going on?

20:13.805 --> 20:17.924
To tell you the truth, I'm having trouble
narrowing down my choice.

20:23.845 --> 20:27.316
I know you want me to pick Miller,
and on paper, I can't argue with that.

20:27.525 --> 20:30.324
Scored higher on the test,
got the experience, the record—

20:30.525 --> 20:32.403
She's African-American,
a woman.

20:32.605 --> 20:35.803
Here's the thing,
Quinn has his attributes too.

20:36.925 --> 20:37.961
Name one.

20:38.165 --> 20:39.201
He's street-smart.

20:40.205 --> 20:42.083
Look, I know what's going on here.

