- That's your neighbour, right?
- Yes.

40:48.125 --> 40:50.845
What happened with Susan?
Wyman break up with her?

40:51.045 --> 40:52.843
Yeah. Yeah, he did.

40:53.485 --> 40:54.521
So it's a win.

40:54.765 --> 40:57.121
Why do you look like someone
just ran over your dog?

40:57.325 --> 41:00.557
I just got off the phone with her
and she couldn't stop crying.

41:00.965 --> 41:02.479
She thinks it's all her fault,

41:02.685 --> 41:05.564
like somehow, she's not
good enough or something.

41:05.765 --> 41:08.724
Well, she would've caught him
cheating eventually.

41:08.925 --> 41:11.394
The result
would have been the same.

41:11.845 --> 41:15.156
Yeah, but it wouldn't be me
that made her cry.

41:16.165 --> 41:18.521
Jesus, I just feel like shit.

41:19.245 --> 41:21.237
People can't help
sticking their noses in

41:21.445 --> 41:23.198
when it's someone
they care about.

41:23.645 --> 41:25.318
I know.

41:25.525 --> 41:28.165
I know. You tried to tell me.

41:30.965 --> 41:32.957
So does that mean
you care about me?

41:34.405 --> 41:37.876
Only to the extent
that you sign my pay cheque.

41:40.285 --> 41:41.878
Touché.

41:42.085 --> 41:45.681
Okay, what are we gonna read tonight?
Let me guess, <i>Wee Monkeys.</i>

41:45.885 --> 41:47.478
<i>Wee Monkeys!</i>

41:57.285 --> 42:02.201
Before I read to you, I gotta
talk to you about the TV remote.

42:02.405 --> 42:03.805
You said you didn't take it,

42:04.045 --> 42:06.435
but Jamie found it
under your bed.

42:11.005 --> 42:12.359
I didn't mean to break it.

42:12.565 --> 42:14.602
I was pretending
it was a Thunder Blaster

42:14.845 --> 42:17.235
and I dropped it in the kitchen.

42:17.445 --> 42:19.357
Well, yeah, that's okay.
Accidents happen.

42:19.565 --> 42:21.284
But you lied to me.
That's a big deal.

42:21.485 --> 42:23.317
We should never lie.

42:27.285 --> 42:29.117
But, Daddy,

42:29.925 --> 42:31.757
you lie.

42:34.325 --> 42:36.078
What do you mean?

42:48.525 --> 42:51.085
You told me Doggy got lost.

42:51.285 --> 42:53.845
I saw you throw him in the trash.

42:54.045 --> 42:56.355
I had to rescue him.

43:01.005 --> 43:03.042
You're right. I lied.

43:04.645 --> 43:07.877
Doggy got dirty,
and I tried to clean him up,

43:08.085 --> 43:10.805
and when I couldn't,
I threw him away.

43:11.605 --> 43:13.915
I'm sorry I lied to you, Harrison.

43:14.125 --> 43:16.685
That's okay.
But can I keep him?

43:16.885 --> 43:18.524
I really love him.

43:18.725 --> 43:21.160
<i>He's soaked in blood
that links me to a murder.</i>

43:21.365 --> 43:24.119
Yeah, but maybe
he should live under the bed.

43:24.325 --> 43:26.556
Okay.
Okay.

43:26.765 --> 43:27.994
<i>Wee Monkeys.</i>

43:28.205 --> 43:30.162
<i>Wee Monkeys!</i>

43:30.365 --> 43:33.961
<i>It's no accident,
Harrison catching me in a lie.</i>

43:34.965 --> 43:37.355
<i>I can live with my lies,
but how long can Harrison</i>

43:37.565 --> 43:40.125
<i>before he finally sees through?</i>

43:40.365 --> 43:42.163
I should be back
in a few hours.

43:42.365 --> 43:45.119
Sorry to keep you late
on your birthday.

43:45.325 --> 43:48.124
Trust me, it'll probably be
the highlight of my day.

43:48.325 --> 43:51.523
<i>Vogel doesn't want me to kill Zach,
but she's wrong about him.</i>

43:51.725 --> 43:53.876
<i>He deserves nothing but my table.</i>

43:55.005 --> 43:56.803
<i>He's here.</i>

44:01.645 --> 44:02.761
Hey, Zach, it's Dexter.

44:26.405 --> 44:28.078
<i>Where is he?</i>

44:35.645 --> 44:39.400
<i>Why would Zach buy a car
for $1200?</i>

44:39.605 --> 44:42.120
<i>Because the one mistake
he made with Norma Rivera</i>

44:42.365 --> 44:44.755
<i>was showing up to kill her
in a red Porsche.</i>

44:44.965 --> 44:47.355
<i>He's going to kill Sofia tonight.</i>

45:04.685 --> 45:06.165
<i>Cypress Harbour Yacht Club.</i>
Hi.

45:06.365 --> 45:09.244
Could you tell me
if Sofia Fuentes is working tonight?

45:09.445 --> 45:12.199
<i>She gets off here in a few minutes.</i>
Thank you.

45:32.245 --> 45:35.238
<i>Zach, waiting to make his move.</i>

45:45.685 --> 45:49.076
<i>And Quinn,
still trying to prove he's a good cop.</i>

45:59.965 --> 46:01.797
Hey, Dex.
<i>Hey.</i>

46:02.005 --> 46:05.362
Look, this is probably
none of my business,

46:05.565 --> 46:08.285
but I feel like I should
tell you about Quinn.

46:08.965 --> 46:10.001
Okay.

46:10.245 --> 46:12.202
He thinks you're gonna
break up with him.

46:12.405 --> 46:13.805
<i>Break up with him? Why?</i>

46:14.045 --> 46:15.843
Because he didn't make sergeant.

46:16.845 --> 46:18.074
That's crazy.

46:18.285 --> 46:19.435
Why would he think that?

46:19.645 --> 46:23.719
Maybe you should, um, invite him over.
I think he's feeling pretty down.

46:23.965 --> 46:25.763
<i>Yeah. Yeah, of course.</i>

46:26.245 --> 46:29.397
Thanks, Dex, for calling.
That really is so sweet of you.

46:29.645 --> 46:30.795
Sure.

46:50.725 --> 46:53.285
<i>Quinn problem solved.</i>

46:55.045 --> 46:56.115
<i>And there's Sofia.</i>

47:04.045 --> 47:05.638
<i>Zach's father.</i>

47:07.005 --> 47:11.204
<i>Sofia is Hamilton's mistress,
just like Norma before her.</i>

47:38.485 --> 47:40.442
<i>What is he doing?</i>

48:12.645 --> 48:13.795
Hey.

48:14.005 --> 48:15.564
I know what you're doing.

48:15.765 --> 48:16.960
Quinn.

48:17.645 --> 48:20.114
You playing detective?
Watching Zach?

48:22.445 --> 48:23.799
Yeah, you caught me.

48:24.045 --> 48:27.482
I'm going to see Jamie.
Keep an eye on Zach.

48:35.685 --> 48:38.439
Jesus. What the fuck?

48:38.685 --> 48:40.517
What are you doing?

48:43.325 --> 48:45.681
Why were you going
to kill your father?

48:45.885 --> 48:49.401
What? I wasn't trying to kill my—
I know you killed Norma Rivera.

48:49.605 --> 48:53.235
I thought you were going to kill Sofia,
but you were going after your father.

48:53.445 --> 48:55.164
Why?
You're crazy.

48:55.365 --> 48:57.880
I didn't try and kill my father.

48:58.525 --> 49:01.199
You tell me one more lie,
and I'll kill you.

49:03.205 --> 49:04.798
I had to.

49:05.045 --> 49:07.196
Why?
Because he's killing my mother.

49:08.365 --> 49:11.437
She's drinking herself to death
because of him.

49:11.845 --> 49:13.802
Over the years,
one affair after another,

49:14.005 --> 49:16.565
and he doesn't
even try and hide it.

49:17.325 --> 49:19.157
I thought killing Norma
would put an end to it,

49:19.325 --> 49:21.237
but two days later,

49:21.445 --> 49:23.562
he's banging some hostess
from the club.

49:25.045 --> 49:26.718
I knew if I wanted it to stop,

49:26.925 --> 49:29.121
I had to kill Dad.

49:31.645 --> 49:33.796
So that's what this is all about,

49:34.005 --> 49:36.474
you trying to protect your mother?

49:36.805 --> 49:38.478
You actually care about her?

49:39.125 --> 49:41.356
Of course I do. She's my mother.

49:45.245 --> 49:48.443
But showing up at crime scenes,

49:49.565 --> 49:51.841
accidents,

49:53.085 --> 49:54.758
taking pictures of all the blood.

49:54.965 --> 49:56.797
This is about more than
just your mother.

49:57.005 --> 49:58.564
No, I had to protect her.

49:58.805 --> 50:01.195
Yeah, I believe you.

50:01.645 --> 50:04.035
But you killed because you want to kill.
No.

50:04.365 --> 50:06.277
Yes.

50:08.205 --> 50:10.765
To take a living person

50:11.685 --> 50:13.756
and make them dead,

50:15.725 --> 50:18.718
imagining that you can
actually hear the moment

50:18.925 --> 50:21.315
when their heart stops beating,

50:22.285 --> 50:25.881
smell the blood
as it pools across the floor.

50:30.965 --> 50:32.877
I can't help it.

50:36.325 --> 50:38.965
It just builds up inside me

50:39.285 --> 50:41.277
all these years.

50:41.485 --> 50:44.239
But Norma was the first time
I ever followed through.

50:44.445 --> 50:46.323
And how was it,

50:46.965 --> 50:48.445
once you'd killed her?

50:50.605 --> 50:54.121
It felt like this huge weight

50:54.365 --> 50:56.641
was lifted off my chest,

50:56.845 --> 51:02.159
this release of something
horrible inside me.

51:04.845 --> 51:07.440
Like you were finally in control.

51:07.645 --> 51:09.284
Yes.

51:15.485 --> 51:17.954
You should just
go ahead and kill me.

51:19.965 --> 51:21.001
Why?

51:21.205 --> 51:23.845
Because if you don't,
I know I'll do it again.

51:27.005 --> 51:31.284
I don't want to be like this,
but I can't help it.

51:33.045 --> 51:34.684
I just am.

51:34.885 --> 51:36.877
I'm some kind of freak.

51:37.085 --> 51:38.804
A monster.

51:39.805 --> 51:41.239
Yes.

51:43.885 --> 51:45.877
You haven't told anyone else
about this?

51:46.125 --> 51:48.082
Besides Dr. Vogel.

51:48.285 --> 51:50.925
No, I couldn't.

51:51.485 --> 51:53.954
You never had a Harry.

51:55.045 --> 51:56.718
A what?

51:57.205 --> 51:59.401
Someone to talk to.

52:02.845 --> 52:04.962
Someone to teach you.

52:08.205 --> 52:10.401
<i>Some things happen to us
by accident.</i>

52:10.645 --> 52:13.797
<i>Others are choices.</i>

52:14.285 --> 52:17.357
<i>There are parts of me that I can
never share with my own son.</i>

52:17.565 --> 52:19.443
<i>But with Zach,</i>

52:19.965 --> 52:21.843
<i>could I teach him?</i>

52:22.045 --> 52:24.082
<i>Am I ready for this,</i>

52:24.325 --> 52:27.204
<i>to be a spiritual father?</i>

52:30.525 --> 52:34.405
So how'd your sting go with Elway?

52:36.165 --> 52:37.963
Terribly.

52:38.685 --> 52:40.438
Didn't work out?

52:41.045 --> 52:43.435
No, it worked out fine, but—

52:44.045 --> 52:45.638
What?

52:48.485 --> 52:50.238
He likes me.

52:50.605 --> 52:52.039
Oh.

52:52.645 --> 52:53.795
That's a bad thing?

52:54.005 --> 52:57.521
Well, he likes me because he doesn't
know a fucking thing about me.

52:58.405 --> 53:02.479
"Yeah, I killed two people
and tried to kill myself and my brother.

53:02.685 --> 53:05.200
But, sorry, what kind of wine
would you like to order?"

53:05.405 --> 53:08.125
I mean, what the fuck?

53:08.325 --> 53:11.682
Yeah, I kind of know what you mean.

53:11.885 --> 53:14.161
How are things with Cassie?

53:15.085 --> 53:16.519
Um...

53:17.365 --> 53:19.482
I don't think there's
much of a future there.

53:19.685 --> 53:22.519
Maybe the Morgans just
aren't meant for relationships.

53:22.765 --> 53:24.802
Yeah, maybe not.

53:27.885 --> 53:29.114
But, hey, life is good.

53:29.325 --> 53:31.760
I'm feeling optimistic
for the first time in a while.

53:31.965 --> 53:34.844
I'm even thinking about
taking on a kind of...

53:35.365 --> 53:36.845
Intern.

53:38.045 --> 53:39.559
Hm...

53:40.925 --> 53:42.882
Well, that's a big step for you, right?

53:43.085 --> 53:47.045
Letting some novice
into your private lab.

53:47.285 --> 53:48.799
Yeah.

53:51.645 --> 53:53.602
Hey, are you okay?

53:53.805 --> 53:55.956
I don't feel so good.

53:56.645 --> 53:58.443
What's wrong?

53:58.805 --> 54:01.081
I feel kind of dizzy.

54:01.285 --> 54:02.639
Deb?

54:08.045 --> 54:09.957
Hello, Dexter.

54:14.005 --> 54:15.962
Remember me?

